description.narrative: In total, 4,734 adolescents (648 boys, 4,086 girls) who were enrolled in UNICEF-supported adolescent empowerment programmes over the year benefited from at least one targeted intervention in eight selected counties of Liberia (Montserrado, Margibi, Grand Bassa, Nimba, River Cess, Grand Cape Mount, Lofa and Grand Gedeh). The core package of the targeted interventions comprised life skills, vocational skills trainings and alternative basic education tutorials, among others. Compared with 2018, there was a threefold increase in terms of the number of adolescents reached | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
